  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI have a component that uses many contexts. I can use these contexts inside the `render` method without any problems using the `Context.Consumer` wrapper. But I can't access contexts in life-cycle methods such as `componentDidMount` or `constructor`, for instance. I found a [solution](https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/12397#issuecomment-375501574) that is based on using a HOC. Is it an officially recommended way?",
